<TITLE> Zafar Iqbal's car crashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Jan 15 (bdnews24.com)--Dr Muhammed Zafar Iqbal, famed writer and professor of the Shahjalal University of Science and Technology, was slightly injured in a car crash on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway on Friday. Sub-inspector Golam Faruk, in charge of Brahmanbaria's Islampur Police Camp, said the microbus carrying Iqbal and his colleague, Dr Sujoy Chakrabarti, to a programme in Comilla, from Sylhet, crashed into the rear of a truck while overtaking it in the early hours of Friday. Dr Iqbal told bdnews24.com after the accident that he had returned home with minor injuries to his shoulder and hand. However, colleague Dr Chakrabarty received substantial injuries. Sheikh Kabirul Islam, officer in charge of Madhabpur Police Station, said Dr Chakrabarty was initially taken to Madhabpur hospital and then to SylhetM A G Osmani Medical College and Hospital (SMCH) where he is still under treatment. bdnew
